
[1]porcellanite

   POR'CELLANITE, n. A silicious mineral, a species of jasper, of various
   colors. It seems to be formed accidentally in coal mines which have
   indurated and semi-vitrified beds of coal-shale or slate-clay. It is
   sometimes marked with vegetable impressions of a brick red color.
